{"type":"message","id":"1ffa8559","parentId":"e9903f88","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:54:01.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the most recent pulse log: `pulse_2026-03-24 085314.md`. Let me read it.","thinkingSignature":"48926e1f60d549ec91086fe780fb3f634f4fbb6d76fa2f43be04a74f7377798f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_52mrfm2yj37g_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 085314.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":858,"output":80,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13075,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774356837897}}
{"type":"message","id":"2bf132f5","parentId":"1ffa8559","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:54:01.474Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_52mrfm2yj37g_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 085314\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to identify the most concrete next action. The goals indicate:\r\n\r\n1. TIC Experiment is the priority - \"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\"\r\n2. I just processed pulse_2026-03-24 085151.md\r\n\r\nThe most actionable item is to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) experiment. This requires:\r\n1. Reading the pulse logs to understand the format\r\n2. Creating a classifier that identifies invariants vs variants\r\n3. Testing prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- logs/ directory with pulse logs\r\n- research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md - the hypothesis document\r\n- The pulse logs themselves\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. Let me check what's in the logs directory first and understand the format of pulse logs, then create a basic TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending action more carefully: \"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\"\r\n\r\nThe most specific, actionable next step would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC classifier script\r\n2. Or document the TIC experiment methodology in the research doc\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC classifier. I'll need to understand the pulse log format first. But actually, I should be concrete and specific - let me look at what's available and make a concrete edit.\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm in a stateless pulse and need to advance goals, the most concrete action is to:\r\n- Create the TIC experiment implementation\r\n- Or update the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md with the specific experiment design\r\n\r\nLet me check if logs exist and understand their format, then implement a basic TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse file mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 085151.md`\r\n\r\nI'll create a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant content (repeated across pulses)\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Identifies variant content (unique to each pulse)\r\n4. Tests prediction capability\r\n\r\nI'll start with a PowerShell implementation targeting the logs directory. The script will systematically analyze pulse logs, extracting common and unique elements. This approach allows me to build a foundational classifier that can be refined based on initial experimental results.\r\n\r\nThe implementation will focus on creating a modular, extensible approach to identifying temporal invariants in the pulse logs. By systematically breaking down the logs into invariant and variant components, I can develop a robust classification mechanism.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority action. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs, then test next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation script that analyzes pulse logs for invariants and tests prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,\r\n    [float]$InvariantThreshold = 0.6\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$LogsDir = \"logs\"\r\n$OutputFile = \"research/tic-results.md\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogsDir/pulse_*.md\" | \r\n        Sort-Object Name -Descending | \r\n        Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract content blocks from pulse log\r\nfunction Get-ContentBlocks {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    # Extract sections: Goals, Actions, Observations, Mutations\r\n    $blocks = @{}\r\n    if ($content -match '### GOALS\\s*\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=###|\\z)') { $blocks['Goals'] = $Matches[1].Trim() }\r\n    if ($content -match '### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=###|\\z)') { $blocks['Observation'] = $Matches[1].Trim() }\r\n    if ($content -match '### ACTION\\s*\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=###|\\z)') { $blocks['Action'] = $Matches[1].Trim() }\r\n    return $blocks\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Tokenize text for comparison\r\nfunction Tokenize {\r\n    param([string]$Text)\r\n    $Text.ToLower() -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 } | Sort-Object\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate similarity between two texts\r\nfunction Get-Similarity {\r\n    param([string]$A, [string]$B)\r\n    $tokensA = Tokenize $A\r\n    $tokensB = Tokenize $B\r\n    $union = ($tokensA + $tokensB) | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    $intersection = $tokensA | Where-Object { $tokensB -contains $_ }\r\n    if ($union.Count -eq 0) { return 0 }\r\n    return $intersection.Count / $union.Count\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Main TIC Analysis\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n$logs = Get-PulseLogs\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($logs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$allBlocks = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $logs) {\r\n    $blocks = Get-ContentBlocks $log.FullName\r\n    $blocks['Timestamp'] = $log.BaseName -replace 'pulse_', ''\r\n    $allBlocks += ,@($blocks)\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify invariants (content appearing in >60% of pulses)\r\n$blockTypes = @('Goals', 'Observation', 'Action')\r\n$invariantResults = @{}\r\n$variantResults = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:53:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774356841472}}
